            <title>[PIG-1084] Pig CookBook documentation &quot;Take Advantage of Join Optimization&quot; additions:Merge and Skewed Join</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PIG-1084</link>
                <project id="12310730" key="PIG">Pig</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Hi all,&lt;br/&gt;
 We have a host of Join optimizations that have been implemented recently in Pig to improve performance. These include:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://hadoop.apache.org/pig/docs/r0.5.0/piglatin_reference.html#JOIN&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://hadoop.apache.org/pig/docs/r0.5.0/piglatin_reference.html#JOIN&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;1) Merge Join&lt;br/&gt;
2) Skewed Join&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It would be nice to mention the Merge Join and Skewed join in the following section on the PigCookBook&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://hadoop.apache.org/pig/docs/r0.5.0/cookbook.html#Take+Advantage+of+Join+Optimization&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://hadoop.apache.org/pig/docs/r0.5.0/cookbook.html#Take+Advantage+of+Join+Optimization&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Can we update this release 0.6??&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks&lt;br/&gt;
Viraj&lt;/p&gt;</description>
